The paper deals with the formal verification of time-varying nonlinear ODE systems subject to uncertainty, which is a problem that arises in many areas of computer science, including systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer engineering (cs.CE), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of optimal control theory to provide solutions for the family of inhomogeneous continuous time Markov decision processes also suggests a connection to the control and optimization literature in cs.SY and cs.DS.
